The paper deals with the problem of finding coordinated paths for multiple mobile agents in a 2D environment, which is a classic problem in robotics and falls under the category of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of reactive techniques and sampling-based iterative algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the use of planning algorithms, which are commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
